Westville local company CHEP has joined arms with the Robin Hood Foundation to spread some love this month. RHF coordinator Kim Griffith Jones of said, ” The foundation will be visiting the elderly of Issy Geshen in Lamontville and those of The Ark where we will be giving some goodies donated by CHEP. “The goodies are toiletries just to put smiles on the elderlies faces as part of our spread the love initiative.” Jones said other companies and individuals that would like to come on board are more than welcome to. If you’d like to get involved please email Kim on info@robinhoodfoundation.
